{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "One of the main radical innovations in transformer technology is the development of large-scale, pretrained language models, referred to as Generative Pretraining Transformers (GPTs), such as OpenAI's GPT series, from GPT-1 in 2018 to ChatGPT-4 in 2023, capable of generating human-like content (OpenAI, 2015, 2022); Google's Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT) model (Devlin et al., 2018); Microsoft Copilot (Mehdi, 2023); etc.",
    "These pretrained models can be used for specific NLP tasks with reduced additional training data, making them highly effective for a wide range of NLP applications, such as (cf.",
    "Assael et al., 2022; Kariampuzha et al., 2023): machine translation document summarization document generation named entity recognition biological sequence analysis writing computer code based on requirements expressed in natural language video understanding computer vision, protein folding applications, etc.",
    "Overall, then, advances in computer science have led to the advent of the large language model (LLM, Bowman, 2023).",
    "In this domain, the new technology of transformers is directed at modeling some activities of the human brain and has led to the new research field of generative AI -software that can create plausible and sophisticated text, images, and computer code at a level that mimics human ability (Pinaya et al., 2023; Tojin et al., 2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Overall, then, advances in computer science have led to the advent of the large language model (LLM, Bowman, 2023).",
    "In this domain, the new technology of transformers is directed at modeling some activities of the human brain and has led to the new research field of generative AI -software that can create plausible and sophisticated text, images, and computer code at a level that mimics human ability (Pinaya et al., 2023; Tojin et al., 2023)."
  ]
